The ANC councillor was elected as regional chairperson in Nelson Mandela Bay earlier this month despite being warned not to stand. JOHANNESBURG The African National Congress (ANC) in Nelson Mandela Bay has confirmed that its newly elected chair Andile Lungisa will step down with immediate effect. The ANC councillor, who s also a provincial executive committee (PEC) member, was elected as regional chairperson earlier this month despite being warned not to stand. This is because of the post he holds in the PEC.Lungisa called for the NEC to rule on his election which saw ANC secretary-general Gwede Mantashe saying he had broken party rules by contesting the position.More details to follow.